============================================================

All 25 tests pass. Here's what the self-review addressed:

**Pre-merge one-continuation limit** — Added a comment documenting that only one continuation line per preceding line is merged. Three-line splits via chained continuation tokens fall through to the existing 2-line/3-line join candidates instead.

**`survivingJoins` comment staleness** — Updated the comment to accurately describe the block's post-Change-1 role: the Baked Eggs case is now handled by pre-merging; this block covers the rarer case where a continuation join was generated as a 2/3-line candidate and its prefix also survived threshold independently.

**Change 3 `<= 2` threshold** — Documented that position ≤ 2 covers "within the first two non-empty document lines, allowing for one blank line between title and subtitle".

**Change 3 ordering** — Documented explicitly why it runs after dedup but before the multi-title guard, and why `allCapsCandidates.length === 1` is the correct safety valve for multi-recipe pages.
