{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RsaQdCkevHbMmWyLYuFZF3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 25 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Change 1 — Pre-merge continuation lines** (`buildCandidates`): Lines starting with `/&+:(` are merged into the preceding line before any candidate generation. This means \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" enters the pool as a single `origin: \"single\"` candidate rather than relying on a fragile 5-step join survival chain.\n\n**Change 2 — Ingredient-gap detection in multi-title guard**: When `allCapsSelected.length >= 2`, each non-first ALL_CAPS heading is checked: if it's immediately followed (within 2 lines) by ingredient-like content (measurement words or lines starting with digits), it's classified as a section header. All non-first headings must be section headers for the rule to fire — this keeps CHLEBEK while correctly returning both FINNISH titles (which are followed by body text, not ingredients).\n\n**Change 3 — First-line mixed-case title protection**: After dedup and before the multi-title guard: if a mixed-case candidate at position 0 passes the threshold, and the only ALL_CAPS candidate is at position ≤ 2, the ALL_CAPS line is treated as a subtitle/transliteration and removed. Fixes bilingual cookbook pages.\n\n**Change 4 (eval harness)** — Already implemented: `title-loop.py` already had `normalize_separators` applied in `titles_match`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1731,"cache_read_input_tokens":79981,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1731},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52016906-9333-4309-a52f-615c04047092","uuid":"fc35a56d-16ca-45ee-89b1-f0ae3338f59a"}
