{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TaktsW7irnREuap4RtPqu1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Agent Instructions\n     2→\n     3→## Dependency Management\n     4→\n     5→**Use NPM only.** Do not use PNPM or YARN for this project.\n     6→\n     7→All package management operations must be executed via `npm`:\n     8→\n     9→- Install dependencies: `npm install`\n    10→- Add packages: `npm install <package>`\n    11→- Remove packages: `npm uninstall <package>`\n    12→- Run scripts: `npm run <script>`\n    13→\n    14→## TypeScript Code Style\n    15→\n    16→**Explicit Return Types Required.** All exported functions in `.ts` and `.tsx` files must have explicitly typed return values.\n    17→\n    18→**Array Type Notation.** Use `Array<T>` notation instead of `T[]` for all array types:\n    19→\n    20→- Correct: `Array<string>`, `Array<Recipe>`, `Promise<Array<User>>`\n    21→- Incorrect: `string[]`, `Recipe[]`, `Promise<User[]>`\n    22→\n    23→**Semantic Type Aliases Required.** Use semantic type aliases from `@/lib/types/primitives` instead of primitive `string` types for domain concepts:\n    24→\n    25→- Use `RecipeId` or `PhotoId` for identifiers (not `string`)\n    26→- Use `PhotoUri`, `ImageUri`, `FileUri`, or `DataUrl` for URIs (not `string`)\n    27→- Use `StorageKey` for storage keys (not `string`)\n    28→- Only use bare `string` for truly generic text content (titles, descriptions, messages)\n    29→\n    30→## React Hooks\n    31→\n    32→**Memoization Required.** All custom React hooks must implement proper memoization:\n    33→\n    34→- Wrap all returned functions in `useCallback`\n    35→- Wrap all returned objects in `useMemo`\n    36→\n    37→## Import Paths\n    38→\n    39→**Use Path Aliases.** Always prefer `@/` imports over relative imports `../../`:\n    40→\n    41→- Allowed: `../sibling` (one level above)\n    42→- Required: `@/platform/theme/useTheme` instead of `../../../platform/theme/useTheme`\n    43→\n    44→## React Imports\n    45→\n    46→**Import JSX Type Directly.** All `.tsx` files must import the JSX type for component return type annotations:\n    47→\n    48→- Use: `import { type JSX } from \"react\";`\n    49→- For component return types: `function Component(): JSX.Element`\n    50→- Combine with other React imports: `import { useState, useEffect, type JSX } from \"react\";`\n    51→- Do NOT import the default `React` export unless you specifically need it (e.g., for `React.memo`, `React.forwardRef`)\n    52→\n    53→## React Components\n    54→\n    55→**No React.FC.** Do not use `React.FC` or `React.FunctionComponent` type annotations:\n    56→\n    57→- Use regular function declarations with explicit return types\n    58→- Correct: `export function Component(props: Props): JSX.Element`\n    59→- Incorrect: `export const Component: React.FC<Props> = (props) => {}`\n    60→\n    61→**Inline Props and Return Types.** All component and hook interfaces must be defined inline in the function declaration:\n    62→\n    63→- Define component props inline: `function Component(props: { title: string; onPress: () => void }): JSX.Element`\n    64→- Define hook return types inline: `function useData(): { data: string[]; loading: boolean }`\n    65→- Define hook parameter types inline: `function useApi(config: { url: string; method: string }): void`\n    66→- Do NOT define separate interfaces for single-use props or return types\n    67→- Keep interfaces only when they are exported or shared across multiple functions\n    68→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ht4X3Td1AcwwJ3k4zJifoM","session_id":"52016906-9